1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,350 --> 00:01:42,229
[I Don't Want to Be Friends With You]

3
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:44,210
Drive safely, Mr Zhang.

4
00:01:44,289 --> 00:01:45,250
Bye-bye.

5
00:01:46,780 --> 00:01:47,660
Who is he?

6
00:01:48,130 --> 00:01:49,410
A client.

7
00:01:49,660 --> 00:01:50,729
What kind of client?

8
00:01:51,530 --> 00:01:52,810
It's none of your business.

9
00:01:52,900 --> 00:01:54,280
You can't understand even if I tell you.

10
00:01:54,380 --> 00:01:56,009
Who says I don't understand?

11
00:01:56,460 --> 00:01:57,890
Don't treat me like a child.

12
00:01:57,979 --> 00:01:59,289
What am I supposed to think of you?

13
00:01:59,380 --> 00:02:01,370
You have agreed to be friends with me.

14
00:02:01,450 --> 00:02:03,400
Who has agreed with you, Li Jin Bu?

15
00:02:03,650 --> 00:02:05,250
You're my daughter.

16
00:02:05,340 --> 00:02:06,690
And I'm your mother.

17
00:02:06,780 --> 00:02:08,330
It will never change.

18
00:02:10,860 --> 00:02:12,490
Li Qing Tong, how can you say so?

19
00:02:12,580 --> 00:02:14,810
I regard you as a friend but
you regard me as your daughter.

20
00:02:16,040 --> 00:02:20,820
[Episode 7: I Treat You as a Friend,
But You Treat Me as a Daughter?]

21
00:02:21,540 --> 00:02:22,530
Mum, I'm home.

22
00:02:22,740 --> 00:02:23,620
Wu Zhi Xun.

23
00:02:24,260 --> 00:02:25,140
You come in here.

24
00:02:31,050 --> 00:02:32,040
What did you do?

25
00:02:32,900 --> 00:02:33,930
In the library.

26
00:02:34,220 --> 00:02:35,200
Are you sure?

27
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:38,690
What's the matter?

28
00:02:40,460 --> 00:02:41,340
Wu Zhi Xun.

29
00:02:41,930 --> 00:02:44,120
You've learned to lie to your
parents now, haven't you?

30
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:45,680
What's the lie?

31
00:02:46,100 --> 00:02:47,200
Let him speak for himself.

32
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:48,730
Where have you been?

33
00:02:48,940 --> 00:02:50,590
He said he went to the library.

34
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:52,360
I saw him outside the hospital.

35
00:02:52,810 --> 00:02:54,610
What did you do in the hospital at night?

36
00:02:54,940 --> 00:02:55,970
Who are the two girls

37
00:02:56,060 --> 00:02:56,940
that go along with you?

38
00:02:57,260 --> 00:02:58,310
Two girls?

39
00:02:58,400 --> 00:02:59,450
What happened?

40
00:03:00,260 --> 00:03:01,490
A classmate was injured.

41
00:03:01,660 --> 00:03:02,370
And I was just passing by.

42
00:03:02,460 --> 00:03:03,720
So I took her to the hospital.

43
00:03:03,980 --> 00:03:05,330
Then why did you lie to your parents?

44
00:03:05,860 --> 00:03:07,240
This isn't the first time.

45
00:03:07,780 --> 00:03:10,130
You've been coming back
late every night these days.

46
00:03:10,620 --> 00:03:11,890
I have called the school.

47
00:03:11,970 --> 00:03:13,370
There are no extra lessons.

48
00:03:14,020 --> 00:03:15,280
Where have you been these nights?

49
00:03:15,660 --> 00:03:16,530
What have you done?

50
00:03:16,620 --> 00:03:17,560
Zhi Xun.

51
00:03:17,660 --> 00:03:18,730
You tell Mum.

52
00:03:18,860 --> 00:03:20,760
Are the two girls friends of yours?

53
00:03:21,060 --> 00:03:22,840
Just the punks at his school.

54
00:03:23,180 --> 00:03:24,810
Is there anyone worth making friends?

55
00:03:25,290 --> 00:03:27,600
You should have great ambitions.

56
00:03:27,810 --> 00:03:29,650
Now you hang out with them.

57
00:03:29,780 --> 00:03:31,120
What are you going to do in the future?

58
00:03:31,540 --> 00:03:32,420
Zhi Xun.

59
00:03:32,700 --> 00:03:33,450
We shouldn't

60
00:03:33,530 --> 00:03:35,810
play with those ignorant students.

61
00:03:35,900 --> 00:03:36,570
Mum.

62
00:03:36,660 --> 00:03:38,040
They're my classmates,

63
00:03:38,140 --> 00:03:39,770
not the ignorant punks.

64
00:03:40,130 --> 00:03:41,170
How dare you talk back to me.

65
00:03:41,500 --> 00:03:43,850
You learn to lie and
talk back to your parents.

66
00:03:43,970 --> 00:03:46,290
Did your friends teach you to do this?

67
00:03:46,380 --> 00:03:48,250
You just hang out with them.

68
00:03:48,340 --> 00:03:49,650
You'll never

69
00:03:49,740 --> 00:03:51,170
get out of this small town in your life.

70
00:03:51,250 --> 00:03:52,890
Small town, small town.

71
00:03:52,980 --> 00:03:54,329
Aren't you in a small town?

72
00:03:54,420 --> 00:03:55,730
Why do you despise them?

73
00:03:55,820 --> 00:03:56,700
You say it again.

74
00:03:58,140 --> 00:03:59,020
Say it again.

75
00:03:59,220 --> 00:04:00,530
Say it again.

76
00:04:00,610 --> 00:04:01,650
OK, OK.

77
00:04:01,740 --> 00:04:03,120
I beg you.

78
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:04,650
Have some fruit.

79
00:04:04,740 --> 00:04:05,640
No.

80
00:04:13,940 --> 00:04:15,490
How did you supervise him at home?

81
00:04:16,010 --> 00:04:17,370
Look at him.

82
00:04:17,700 --> 00:04:19,279
Didn't you even notice anything?

83
00:04:19,820 --> 00:04:22,330
He has already hung out with the punks.

84
00:04:22,540 --> 00:04:24,240
This is the beginning of his downfall.

85
00:04:24,980 --> 00:04:26,530
Look at him now.

86
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:28,370
He only gets first place

87
00:04:28,580 --> 00:04:30,610
in a third-rate high
school in this small town.

88
00:04:30,700 --> 00:04:31,960
Does he think that he is outstanding?

89
00:04:32,260 --> 00:04:34,770
He has no idea how
cruel the outside world is.

90
00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:49,170
Where is Hua?

91
00:04:49,260 --> 00:04:50,250
Why isn't she here?

92
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:55,950
Her leg is injured.

93
00:04:56,040 --> 00:04:57,090
What?

94
00:04:57,740 --> 00:04:58,920
Why?

95
00:05:07,930 --> 00:05:08,930
Li

96
00:05:09,020 --> 00:05:10,130
is too rigid.

97
00:05:10,220 --> 00:05:11,650
He is not flexible.

98
00:05:11,820 --> 00:05:12,850
Wang

99
00:05:12,940 --> 00:05:15,250
often takes him to business dinners.

100
00:05:15,460 --> 00:05:16,650
He refuses to go.

101
00:05:16,780 --> 00:05:18,410
When he goes, he doesn't know what to say,

102
00:05:18,600 --> 00:05:20,160
which makes Wang

103
00:05:20,250 --> 00:05:21,890
embarrassed.

104
00:05:22,030 --> 00:05:22,850
Right.

105
00:05:22,940 --> 00:05:25,690
You know what Li is like.

106
00:05:25,770 --> 00:05:27,490
But he is the salt of the earth.

107
00:05:28,140 --> 00:05:29,210
As for that matter,

108
00:05:29,340 --> 00:05:30,690
you tell Wang to ask again.

109
00:05:30,930 --> 00:05:32,010
Okay.

110
00:05:33,820 --> 00:05:34,450
Hey.

111
00:05:34,540 --> 00:05:35,950
Why don't you call me?

112
00:05:37,020 --> 00:05:38,250
Here, let me help you.

113
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:40,530
What's wrong with the kid?

114
00:05:40,659 --> 00:05:41,850
Her leg is injured.

115
00:05:42,590 --> 00:05:43,250
Hua.

116
00:05:43,340 --> 00:05:43,950
This is

117
00:05:44,030 --> 00:05:45,120
your aunt.

118
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,210
Auntie.

119
00:05:46,300 --> 00:05:47,770
What a pretty girl you are.

120
00:05:47,860 --> 00:05:50,250
This kid is definitely from the big city.

121
00:05:50,340 --> 00:05:52,720
My son often talks about you.

122
00:05:52,980 --> 00:05:54,890
How's my son doing at school?

123
00:05:55,380 --> 00:05:55,930
Good.

124
00:05:56,010 --> 00:05:57,409
If he does anything wrong,

125
00:05:57,500 --> 00:05:58,930
you must tell me.

126
00:05:59,180 --> 00:06:01,510
He always makes trouble.

127
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:03,010
Sit down, sit down.

128
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:03,970
I'm going to help her go to the bathroom.

129
00:06:04,050 --> 00:06:04,930
You sit down.

130
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:06,730
I can do it myself, auntie. I can.

131
00:06:06,810 --> 00:06:07,530
Okay.

132
00:06:07,620 --> 00:06:08,130
Hold on to the wall.

133
00:06:08,220 --> 00:06:09,100
Okay.

134
00:06:09,450 --> 00:06:10,690
Sit down, sit down.

135
00:06:10,900 --> 00:06:11,790
Take a drink of water.

136
00:06:14,050 --> 00:06:14,930
I heard from my son that

137
00:06:15,020 --> 00:06:17,410
she has been living in your house.

138
00:06:18,220 --> 00:06:19,290
Yeah, she has been here.

139
00:06:19,660 --> 00:06:21,050
What's going on with her family?

140
00:06:21,140 --> 00:06:22,840
Her parents don't care about her,

141
00:06:23,460 --> 00:06:24,810
and just leave her with you for nothing.

142
00:06:24,900 --> 00:06:26,280
What kind of parents are they?

143
00:06:26,370 --> 00:06:27,770
That's OK.

144
00:06:28,180 --> 00:06:30,730
She's only a little girl.
She can't eat much.

145
00:06:30,820 --> 00:06:32,210
We can feed her well

146
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:33,250
even if each of us takes one less bite.

147
00:06:33,340 --> 00:06:34,510
It isn't worth quibbling over this.

148
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,930
Well, that still doesn't work.

149
00:06:36,020 --> 00:06:38,210
Look how fast prices are going up now.

150
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:40,450
Why should you raise a daughter for them?

151
00:06:40,540 --> 00:06:42,250
If she's sick or injured,

152
00:06:42,330 --> 00:06:43,650
you have to look after her.

153
00:06:43,740 --> 00:06:45,080
Why should you do this?

154
00:06:45,820 --> 00:06:47,840
Well, because her parents are both abroad.

155
00:06:48,020 --> 00:06:49,250
That poor girl is

156
00:06:49,340 --> 00:06:51,450
alone and has no
relatives and friends here.

157
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:52,130
Besides,

158
00:06:52,220 --> 00:06:53,770
I just give her something to eat.

159
00:06:53,860 --> 00:06:55,000
It's no big deal.

160
00:06:55,300 --> 00:06:56,840
Just be a nice guy.

161
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:58,840
You're the kind of person who loses.

162
00:07:01,020 --> 00:07:01,790
Hua.

163
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:02,770
Be careful.

164
00:07:02,860 --> 00:07:03,290
Okay.

165
00:07:03,380 --> 00:07:03,850
Hua.

166
00:07:03,940 --> 00:07:06,080
What would you like to eat?
Auntie will buy some for you.

167
00:07:06,530 --> 00:07:07,520
Just sit down.

168
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:09,650
Have an orange.

169
00:07:09,980 --> 00:07:10,860
It's sweet.

170
00:07:12,020 --> 00:07:13,530
Come on, come on,
I'll take you on my bike.

171
00:07:14,220 --> 00:07:14,690
Slow down, slow down.

172
00:07:14,780 --> 00:07:15,410
Qing Tong.

173
00:07:15,500 --> 00:07:16,290
Xiao, your bag, Xiao.

174
00:07:16,380 --> 00:07:17,370
Wait for me.

175
00:07:17,460 --> 00:07:18,320
Xiao.

176
00:07:18,410 --> 00:07:19,330
Ba Dan.

177
00:07:19,530 --> 00:07:20,770
Can you take me?

178
00:07:21,160 --> 00:07:22,800
Xiao, your bag, Xiao.

179
00:07:23,490 --> 00:07:25,050
Wait for me.

180
00:07:26,420 --> 00:07:27,690
Well, I'm leaving now.

181
00:07:28,090 --> 00:07:29,410
You can come to our house later

182
00:07:29,500 --> 00:07:31,010
and taste the prawns Wang brings back.

183
00:07:31,100 --> 00:07:32,130
It's so big

184
00:07:32,220 --> 00:07:33,210
and delicious.

185
00:07:33,610 --> 00:07:35,170
I'm not used to the prawns.

186
00:07:36,180 --> 00:07:37,090
Auntie.

187
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:38,280
Mum.

188
00:07:39,820 --> 00:07:40,700
Auntie.

189
00:07:40,820 --> 00:07:42,090
Why are you all here?

190
00:07:42,180 --> 00:07:42,730
Auntie.

191
00:07:42,820 --> 00:07:43,960
We came to see Hua.

192
00:07:44,050 --> 00:07:44,930
Auntie.

193
00:07:45,540 --> 00:07:46,570
Mum, what are you doing here?

194
00:07:46,659 --> 00:07:48,050
What are you doing here?

195
00:07:48,300 --> 00:07:49,090
Hua broke her leg.

196
00:07:49,180 --> 00:07:50,090
I'm here to see her.

197
00:07:51,420 --> 00:07:52,130
Wait a minute.

198
00:07:52,210 --> 00:07:52,730
Mum.

199
00:07:52,820 --> 00:07:53,690
You give me 50 yuan.

200
00:07:53,780 --> 00:07:54,730
For what?

201
00:07:54,820 --> 00:07:56,600
I want to buy some food for Hua.

202
00:07:59,860 --> 00:08:00,290
Okay, Mum.

203
00:08:00,380 --> 00:08:01,560
Well, then you can go home.

204
00:08:01,650 --> 00:08:02,570
I go to that room.

205
00:08:02,650 --> 00:08:03,370
Wild kid.

206
00:08:03,460 --> 00:08:05,370
You didn't care so much when I was sick.

207
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:06,840
Goodbye. Take care.

208
00:08:06,930 --> 00:08:07,810
Bye.

209
00:08:09,860 --> 00:08:10,800
Where did you fall?

210
00:08:10,890 --> 00:08:11,880
It is so serious.

211
00:08:11,980 --> 00:08:13,170
It's not serious.

212
00:08:13,530 --> 00:08:14,850
You don't circle me.

213
00:08:14,940 --> 00:08:16,890
It's like I'm going to die.

214
00:08:18,050 --> 00:08:19,770
Did Chen Jun He do this?

215
00:08:19,860 --> 00:08:20,890
It must be him.

216
00:08:20,980 --> 00:08:22,210
Who else?

217
00:08:22,300 --> 00:08:23,450
Not him.

218
00:08:23,540 --> 00:08:25,050
I just fell by accident.

219
00:08:25,140 --> 00:08:26,490
Li Qing Tong was there.

220
00:08:26,940 --> 00:08:28,770
It was really an accident.

221
00:08:29,340 --> 00:08:30,720
I'll go home and get
you some safflower oil

222
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:32,039
and the medicine my father brings back.

223
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:33,240
No need.

224
00:08:34,179 --> 00:08:35,320
I'm not crippled.

225
00:08:35,740 --> 00:08:37,200
Don't make it so serious.

226
00:08:37,380 --> 00:08:38,570
Mind your own business.

227
00:08:39,980 --> 00:08:41,690
So how do you go to school tomorrow?

228
00:08:41,860 --> 00:08:42,530
I'm okay.

229
00:08:42,620 --> 00:08:43,559
It doesn't matter.

230
00:08:49,660 --> 00:08:50,540
What are you going to do?

231
00:08:53,860 --> 00:08:54,740
Hua.

232
00:08:55,440 --> 00:08:56,890
I asked my mum for 50 yuan.

233
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:58,050
What would you like to eat?

234
00:08:58,740 --> 00:09:00,490
I'd like to have two hamburgers.

235
00:09:00,700 --> 00:09:01,730
What does it matter to you?

236
00:09:01,820 --> 00:09:02,970
You look like a hamburger.

237
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:04,180
You look like chips.

238
00:09:04,260 --> 00:09:05,170
You look like a hamburger.

239
00:09:05,250 --> 00:09:06,210
You look like lettuce.

240
00:09:07,170 --> 00:09:08,060
[Peony Hotel]

241
00:09:08,060 --> 00:09:09,250
The Queen Room is 45 yuan.

242
00:09:09,820 --> 00:09:11,320
Who's going to pay for the 45 yuan?

243
00:09:12,660 --> 00:09:14,010
Give me money, 45 yuan.

244
00:09:14,440 --> 00:09:15,450
OK, I'll pay for it.

245
00:09:16,460 --> 00:09:17,770
Please check in.

246
00:09:22,140 --> 00:09:23,080
Right.

247
00:09:26,580 --> 00:09:28,360
What are you doing?

248
00:09:30,740 --> 00:09:31,690
Write it here.

249
00:09:37,660 --> 00:09:40,000
What are you doing everyday?

250
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:42,250
Day by day.

251
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:32,430
It's the weekend,

252
00:10:32,510 --> 00:10:34,130
and you're here so early for practice.

253
00:10:35,180 --> 00:10:35,970
I can practice on my own.

254
00:10:36,060 --> 00:10:37,050
You don't have to stay with me.

255
00:10:37,260 --> 00:10:37,970
No.

256
00:10:38,060 --> 00:10:39,120
I have my job.

257
00:10:39,210 --> 00:10:40,440
I have promised Hua

258
00:10:40,530 --> 00:10:41,760
to supervise you.

259
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:44,770
You just practice.

260
00:10:44,860 --> 00:10:46,090
I just sit aside and watch.

261
00:10:56,780 --> 00:10:57,730
Coming.

262
00:11:01,650 --> 00:11:02,690
Can you go outside?

263
00:11:03,400 --> 00:11:04,200
What?

264
00:11:04,290 --> 00:11:05,690
I have something to show you.

265
00:11:13,650 --> 00:11:14,290
Where are you from?

266
00:11:14,380 --> 00:11:16,050
Who allowed you to play here?

267
00:11:17,100 --> 00:11:18,350
We've been playing here all the time.

268
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:19,450
Where are you from?

269
00:11:19,540 --> 00:11:20,210
Cut the nonsense.

270
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:22,090
This pitch is ours. Go away.

271
00:11:22,420 --> 00:11:24,560
Why is it yours just
because you say it's yours?

272
00:11:24,650 --> 00:11:25,690
Be reasonable, OK?

273
00:11:25,770 --> 00:11:27,520
We are here first.

274
00:11:27,660 --> 00:11:29,010
Don't you see the back
half of the pitch is still empty?

275
00:11:29,100 --> 00:11:30,050
Why don't you guys play there?

276
00:11:30,140 --> 00:11:31,090
Li Qing Tong.

277
00:11:31,930 --> 00:11:32,810
Never mind.

278
00:11:32,980 --> 00:11:34,850
This girl is so bad-tempered.

279
00:11:34,940 --> 00:11:35,650
Get out of the way.

280
00:11:35,740 --> 00:11:37,130
I won't move.

281
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:38,130
Leave her alone.

282
00:11:38,220 --> 00:11:39,490
Let's play.

283
00:11:42,540 --> 00:11:43,420
I...

284
00:11:46,330 --> 00:11:47,570
What are you doing?

285
00:11:47,900 --> 00:11:49,960
Since you are unreasonable,
I am not reasonable either.

286
00:11:50,220 --> 00:11:50,890
If you continue to play,

287
00:11:50,980 --> 00:11:52,010
I'm going to yell.

288
00:11:52,100 --> 00:11:53,160
I'm angry.

289
00:11:53,250 --> 00:11:54,970
Bro, forget it.

290
00:11:55,060 --> 00:11:55,890
Forget it. A gentleman
doesn't fight with women.

291
00:11:55,980 --> 00:11:57,370
Leave her alone. Let's go.

292
00:11:57,450 --> 00:11:59,050
Bro, I'm telling you.

293
00:11:59,140 --> 00:11:59,930
